This paper deals with the security of quantum encryption schemes, which is a topic that falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses information-theoretic security, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves computational security, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The use of quantum mechanics in encryption schemes suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of quantum information (cs.QI). Finally, the paper discusses the definition of security for encryption schemes, which is a topic in computer engineering (cs.CE).
